--- Part 5: Dimension counting ---
At n=5:
  H values: {1, 3, 5, 9, 11, 13, 15} = 7 distinct values
  Tournaments: 2^10 = 1024
  Type-2 invariants: closed under ΔΔ=0 for disjoint arcs
  Type-4 invariants: vanish on 5th-order alternating sums

  H = I(Ω,2) = 1 + 2α₁ + 4α₂ + 8α₃
  If ΔH = 2Δα₁ + 4Δα₂ + 8Δα₃ (verified), then H = I(Ω,2)
  follows from the IDENTITY of arc-flip calculus and independence poly!

  KEY: The OCF identity H = I(Ω,2) is equivalent to saying that
  the arc-flip derivative of H decomposes into binary-weighted
  derivatives of the independent set counts α_k.

